The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, visited the U.S. Drug Enforcement Administration (DEA) to receive a briefing on the agency's efforts to combat drug abuse and addiction. Pence expressed his gratitude to the DEA and law enforcement personnel for their dedication to protecting American families from the dangers of drug trafficking and criminal syndicates. He emphasized the importance of securing the southern border to prevent the entry of drugs into the country. Pence assured the DEA of the administration's commitment to providing the necessary resources to carry out their missions effectively. He also highlighted the DEA's role in targeting drug trafficking in Venezuela and its contribution to empowering the people of Venezuela in their fight for freedom. Pence closed his remarks with a prayer for the safety and success of the DEA in their efforts to enforce laws and combat drug abuse in the United States.